                        <handDesc>
                            <handNote scope="sole" xml:id="hand-1">
                                <p>The text was copied in a <term type="script">mixed
                                        minuscule</term> script, slanting slightly to the right, in
                                    brown ink, with little variation in letter size.</p>
                                <p>Syllabic abbreviations are not used except the horizontal stroke
                                    for <hi rend="italic">nu</hi>, which appears only at the end of
                                    lines, while superscript word endings do not appear. Breathings
                                    are angular, (but do not appear in the half-H form), and mute <hi rend="italic">iota</hi> is absent. The double grave accent
                                    is in use.</p>
                                <p>Punctuation used includes the lower, middle and upper points and
                                    the lower and middle commas.</p>
                            </handNote>
                        </handDesc>

                        <decoDesc>
                            <decoNote type="plainInit">The beginnings of sections are marked by
                                minor initials in brown ink.</decoNote>
                        </decoDesc>

                        <additions>Line numbers in Arabic numerals have been added every five lines
                            on the <locus from="1r" to="1r">recto</locus>. A note giving a textual
                            citation appears in the upper margin. The fragment has been marked with
                            the present classmark and the former classmark T.18.</additions>
                    </physDesc>

